      <mods:abstract>
        The Impressionist painting by Claude Monet was stolen from the Metropolitan Museum of Art in the 1999 American heist film The Thomas Crown Affair by Thomas Crown (played by Pierce Brosnan). In reality, the painting exists in two versions; one is housed in the National Museum Cardiff in Cardiff, Wales, and the other in the Bridgestone Museum of Art in Tokyo, Japan. 
      </mods:abstract>
